# Tailwind CSS Patterns

## Usage Rules
- Utility classes only in templates — no inline `style=""` unless dynamic values require it
- For dynamic classes, use `:class` binding with a computed or explicit object
- Never mix Tailwind utilities with raw CSS in `<style scoped>` for the same property

## Class Organization (order matters for readability)
```
Layout → Flexbox/Grid → Spacing → Sizing → Typography → Color → Border → Effects → State
```
Example: `flex items-center gap-4 px-6 py-3 w-full text-sm font-medium text-white bg-blue-600 rounded-lg shadow hover:bg-blue-700`

## Component Patterns
- Extract repeated class combinations into a component — not into `@apply`
- Use `@apply` only in base layer styles (e.g., `body`, `h1`) via `src/assets/base.css`
- Responsive prefix order: base → `sm:` → `md:` → `lg:` → `xl:`

## Dark Mode
- Use `dark:` variant — configure `darkMode: 'class'` in `tailwind.config`
- Every color utility used should have a `dark:` counterpart defined

## Do Not
- Do not use arbitrary values `[123px]` unless no token exists — prefer config extension
- Do not use Tailwind for animations that need JS control — use CSS vars + transitions
